509B7_ Hooded knit in lambswool and gauzed bouclé wool. The two yarns create two contrasting colour blocks on the left and right of the knit, and on the upper and lower part of the sleeve. Big Stone Island Compass logo embroidery on chest, made with different stitching and appliqué techniques.

Stone Island _ AW'019'020
MICRO REPS WITH PRIMALOFT® INSULATION TECHNOLOGY
Parka and jacket in a military specification polyester nylon Rep. The weft yarns, thinner in diameter compared to the warp yarns, enable the fabric to be tightly woven in order to obtain a compact, wind-resistant tela. The garment has been padded with a #PrimaLoft® layer, an exclusive blend of ultra-thin fibres providing exceptional insulating capacity. PrimaLoft® is developed to stay drier even when wet. It delivers the highest warmth-to-weight ratio of all synthetic insulations. The fabric is sprayed with a special anti-drop agent.
#StoneIsland

Stone Island _ AW'019'020
44523 GARMENT DYED CRINKLE REPS NY
Hooded bomber jacket, in a padded light nylon rep with an ultra-tight weaving construction. The resin coating of its inner layer makes it wind-resistant and mildly water-resistant. Due to uneven penetration, the dye bath gives the resin-treated fabric a slightly crinkled appearance on the surface. The addition of a special agent to the dye formula makes the piece anti-drop.
#StoneIsland #GarmentDyed

Stone Island _ AW'019'020
70449 DAVID-TC WITH PANNO JACQUARD_ DETACHABLE LINING
Fishtail Parka in David-TC. Starting with an initial star-shaped Japanese polyester/polyamide substrate, garments in David-TC are assembled and then simultaneously dyed and treated with an anti-drop agent. During garment dyeing under pressure at 130°C, the heat radically transforms the structure and feel of the material. The result is beautiful and wearable clothes that combine an industrial feel with a rich and unique tactile experience. The piece features a detachable lining in Panno Jacquard, an 80% recycled wool and 20% nylon cloth, taking inspiration from the military woollen blankets. The graphic striped motif and the Stone Island logo are obtained by jacquard processing.
#StoneIsland #GarmentDyed #DavidTC

Stone Island _ AW'019'020
41629 GORE-TEX PACLITE® PRODUCT TECHNOLOGY WITH PRIMALOFT® INSULATION
Hooded jacket in Gore-Tex Paclite®. The Paclite® product technology is used for lightweight, breathable garments that live up with the Guaranteed to Keep You Dry Gore-Tex promise. The outer face of this highly performing two layer fabric is made of ultra-light polyester made with 50 micro denier yarns, treated with anti-drop technology. It is bonded to a fine membrane extremely breathable, durable, waterproof and totally windproof. The garment is fully seam-taped. Padded with a #PrimaLoft® layer, an exclusive blend of ultra-thin fibres providing exceptional insulating capacity. PrimaLoft® is developed to stay drier even when wet. It delivers the highest warmth-to-weight ratio of all synthetic insulations.
#StoneIsland

Stone Island _ AW'019'020
43031 DAVID LIGHT-TC WITH MICROPILE
Anorak in a lightweight tela made with a Japanese star-shaped cross-section polyester/polyamide yarns with a polyester micro pile layer inside. It is assembled and then dyed under pressure at 130°C. During the garment dye process, the heat radically transforms the material’s feel and structure. The resulting garments combine an industrial appearance with a unique feel.
#StoneIsland #GarmentDyed

Stone Island _ AW'019'020
41028 COMFORT TECH COMPOSITE
Hooded bomber jacket made with an outer and an inner light and super stretch nylon layer. The two highly breathable layers are padded with a comfortable stretchy polyester substrate, optimised for garment dyeing. Garment dyed with original colour recipes with the addition of an anti-drop agent.
#StoneIsland #GarmentDyed

Stone Island_AW’019’020
71321 50 FILI RESINATA DOWN-TC WITH SHEEPSKIN
Parka made of a brushed cotton nylon fabric soaked in a light polyurethane resin for a snappy feel. It undergoes an elaborate double dyeing process, with the addition of an anti-drop agent. The piece is padded with premium feathers specifically treated to withstand the garment dyeing procedure.
#StoneIsland #GarmentDyed

Stone Island is aware of the existence of websites selling fake products. Some even reproduce the brand's trademark and are therefore particularly misleading for consumers. These sites are often registered with a domain comprising the brand name Stone Island, or something similar, and additional words such as ‘jackets’, ‘outlet’ or ‘official’.
It is our priority to defend and protect our customers and our brand image.
This is why we have taken every possible action against the sale of fake products and shut down misleading sites, web pages and social network pages through legal action using two international companies specializing in the fight against counterfeiting: MarkMonitor and React.
Those who have ordered or purchased a fake garment can go to their local authority and contact their bank to, where possible, block payment made to a suspected fraudulent site.

To inform us of a suspected counterfeit product or website, please e-mail anticounterfeiting@spwco.it including a link to the site or the name and location of the retailer.

Our official website is stoneisland.com - as well as the official Stone Island App in North America.
Our sales site in the UK is stoneisland.co.uk.

Furthermore, Stone Island has launched a garment authentication service.
Since the Spring Summer 2014 collection Stone Island has used Certilogo® technology and experience to offer customers the possibility of verifying the authenticity of their Stone Island and Stone Island Shadow Project products, wherever they were purchased, using the 12-digit Certilogo code – on stoneisland.com and certilogo.com - or their mobile phone to scan the QR Code.
The code and QR code are found on the security label inside the garments.
#StoneIsland #FightFakes #AuthenticityProgram

10323 GARMENT DYED CRINKLE REPS NY + RETE ISOLANTE TC
Overshirt in a light nylon rep with an ultra-tight weaving construction.The resin coating of its inner layer makes it wind resistant and mildly water resistant. Due to uneven penetration, the dye bath gives the resin-treated fabric a slightly crinkled appearance on the surface.The garment is lined with a special polyester technical mesh specifically gauzed to allow breathability and insulating functions. 
11036 NYLON METAL RIPSTOP + RETE ISOLANTE TC
Overshirt in Nylon Ripstop.The trilobate structure of the nylon yarn, with its grey weft and white ready to dye warp colours, is the grounds of the distinctive metallic and tonic sheen of Nylon Metal, one of the most versatile fabrics born of Stone Island textile research.The fabric has been resin treated inside to achieve a mild wind and water resistance.The finished piece undergoes an elaborate double dye procedure providing different tones, intensities and colours to the fibres and textile accessories of the garment.The garment is lined with a special polyester technical mesh specifically gauzed to allow breathability and fulfill insulating functions.
#StoneIsland #GarmentDyed

Stone Island_AW’019’020
41349 DAVID-TC WITH SHEEPSKIN _ DETACHABLE LINING
Hooded jacket in David-TC. Beginning with a star-shaped cross-section Japanese polyester/polyamide substrate, garments in David-TC are sewn and then simultaneously garment dyed and treated with an anti-drop agent. During the dye process, under pressure at 130°C, the fabric undergoes heat-induced compression, radically transforming its hand and body for a truly unique tactile experience. The piece features a detachable lining with sheepskin front.
Hood with drawstring, the rim is edged in David Light.
#StoneIsland #GarmentDyed #DavidTC
